               <p>CHARLES WARTON. I am an <rs id="t18321018-231-viclabel1290" type="occupation">auctioneer</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-231-victim2000 t18321018-231-viclabel1290"></join>, and live in Threadneedle-street. On the 5th of October, about ten o'clock in the morning, I was in <placeName id="t18321018-231-crimeloc1291">New-street, Covent-garden</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-231-crimeloc1291" type="placeName" value="New-street, Covent-garden"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18321018-231-crimeloc1291" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18321018-231-off1288 t18321018-231-crimeloc1291"></join>, and had my handkerchief in my pocket; Ruffy gave me information, and I missed it - I saw Bridge there, but not Foley.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-231-person2001">
                  JOHN 
                  RUFFY
               <interp inst="t18321018-231-person2001" type="surname" value="RUFFY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-231-person2001" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-231-person2001" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an oilman, and live in James-street, Covent-garden. I was in New-street, and saw the prisoners together; my attention was attracted by Foley beckoning to a boy behind him - I watched, and saw Bridge take a handkerchief from the prosecutor's pocket, and put it behind him; Foley was alongside him, and could not help seeing it - I informed the prosecutor, and then pursued; they took different directions - Bridge dropped the handkerchief in the middle of the road, and was taken directly after by the Policeman, who took it up- Foley was brought to the station in about half an hour; I had not seen him do any thing.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-231-person2002">
                  THOMAS 
                  POCOCK
               <interp inst="t18321018-231-person2002" type="surname" value="POCOCK"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-231-person2002" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18321018-231-person2002" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a Policeman. I heard a cry of Stop thief! and saw Bridge running; he put his hand into his bosom, and threw the handkerchief away; I took it up and secured him.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Foley's Defence. I was going to the workhouse for my mother's money, and had the ticket in my hand.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18321018-231-person2003">
                  THOMAS 
                  POCOCK
               <interp inst="t18321018-231-person2003" type="surname" value="POCOCK"></interp>
